              "name": "shanekumpf@gmail.com",
              "key": "shanekumpf@gmail.com",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Shane Kumpf",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Denver"
            },
            "body": "Thanks for taking another look at the library, [~eyang]. It sounds like some improvements have been made, but gaps still exist. The security gaps in the go HDFS client is likely a non-starter for many. I'm inclined to agree that a registry storage driver for HDFS won't be implemented until this gap is fixed and fixing the gap is outside of the scope of YARN. The issue could be reopened if security is properly implemented.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=shanekumpf%40gmail.com",
              "name": "shanekumpf@gmail.com",
              "key": "shanekumpf@gmail.com",
